This is the first time I've ever seen this. This appeared to be a colony of flying insects. There was a rather large patch of area (3rd photo) with little tunnels in sandy soil (last photo). I don't recall seeing any of the flying insects entering or exiting the tunnels, but they were all flying around the area with the tunnels, very low over the ground. What did I see? Bee flies, blow flies? Something else? I'm really curious.

description:
Day 4 of one of the greatest vacations ever! Full journal of nature adventures here: http://www.inaturalist.org/journal/sambiology/9891-vacation-in-california-news-flash-i-like-california

Using the great existing observations from the San Francisco Bay area and species guide to help with the ID's -- but please correct me if I've goofed. Almost ALL of these organisms were new for me! Also, I'll work on these ID's a bit later too.

Really enjoyed spending time at Point Reyes, although it started to rain a little bit, so we had to leave.  I sure want to come back and explore more!
